---
import Base from '../layout/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Now | Joban Mendpara"
  description="What I'm working on"
  class="bg-background"
>
  <div class="h-52 block"></div>
  <div class="max-w-3xl p-4 xl:text-base max-h-fit leading-relaxed md:px-24 min-h-fit flex flex-col justify-around gap-4">
    <a class="items-center text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-200 hover:underline mb-10 flex align-middle w-fit" href="/">
      <span>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-arrow-left" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path>
          <path d="M5 12l14 0"></path>
          <path d="M5 12l6 6"></path>
          <path d="M5 12l6 -6"></path>
        </svg>
      </span>
      Back
    </a>
    <h2 class="text-3xl text-foreground font-bold">Now</h2>
    <hr class="border-t-1 border-primary"/>
    <p>I'm currently working on <em>Open Silo</em> in my spare time.</p>
    <p>
      Open Silo is a WIP SAAS application utilizing the T3 Stack (Typescript, tRPC, TailwindCSS).
      Users will be able to upload documents that will be analyzed by ChatGPT. As users add more documents, "context"
      of the subject matter will develop. Users will be able to query ChatGPT to discern truth from their context.
    </p>
    <p>
      Currently, Open Silo is not available for a demo, but if you have any inquiries I'd love to dive into the code and
      show what I've built and what's to come.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
